com.ibm.avatar.api.tam

Interface MultiModuleMetadata


  • public interface MultiModuleMetadata
    This class provides APIs to retrieve metadata of various AQL elements from the loaded MultiModuleMetadata object. An instance of this type can be obtained by invoking one of the ModuleMetadataFactory.readAllMetaData(String) APIs. This class is similar to ModuleMetadata, except that each object represents metadata associated with a set of modules. This module set is guaranteed to be complete, containing every module that is referenced by the modules in the input module list passed to the constructor.
    See Also:
    ModuleMetadata

        ViewMetadata getViewMetadata(String viewName)

        Parameters:
        viewName - this name can be one of the following: an output alias, an external name (in case of external view), the fully qualified name for modular AQLs, an unqualified view name inside a genericModule(module generate for non-modular AQL code), or the view Document

      • getComment

        String getComment(ModuleMetadata.ElementType type,
                  String name)
           throws InvalidModuleElementException
        Retrieve the text of the AQL doc comment associated with the given element of the given type.
        Parameters:
        type - type of element
        name - qualified name of the element. For elements of type ModuleMetadata.ElementType.VIEW,this name be either be an output alias, fully qualified name,external name (in case of external view), or unqualified name for view inside a genericModule(module generated for non-modular AQL)
        Returns:
        string contains the AQL doc comment associated for given element name
        Throws:
        InvalidModuleElementException - if an element of the given type with the given name does not exist

      • getOutputViews

        String[] getOutputViews()
        Returns a list of names of the views marked as output view through the output view statement. Names returned are either output view aliases created through output view statement's 'as' clause, a view name qualified by containing module name if alias is not declared, or an unqualified view name for genericModule (module compiled from non-modular AQLs).
        Returns:
        an array of output view names

      • getExternalViews

        List<Pair<String,String>> getExternalViews()
        Returns list of all external view name pairs within the module set, where the first element of the pair is the view name as declared in an AQL create external view statement. For modular AQL, the view name returned will be qualified with containing module name; the second argument is the external name as declared in an AQL create external view statement's external_name clause.
        Returns:
        list of external view name pairs
